cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper deals with video understanding and action detection, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves learning spatio-temporal relationships between entities using self-attention on a graph structure, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the AVA dataset, which is a popular benchmark for video understanding and falls under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as entity recognition and attention, which are also used in computational linguistics (cs.CL).
